The paper deals with information-theoretic problems and establishes a general approach for deriving one-shot performance bounds. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with random number generation from correlated sources, which is a topic that falls under Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the quantization idea, which is a topic in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The novel form of "likelihood ratio" mentioned in the abstract suggests that the paper may also belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with performance bounds, which is a topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG).
